{"page_content": "3 Definitions and Abbreviations\n\nFAIR\n\nFindable, Accessible, Interopable, and Reusable\n\nFAIR-DSM FAIRplus DataSet Maturity Model\n\nMetadata Data that provides information about other data (Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata).\n\n4 Method\n\nGeneral\n\nAssessment of FAIRness level of dataset\n\nThe principles of FAIR have been applied across multiple domains, including life sciences and drug discovery. Given the complex requirements for FAIR data and its associated metadata, a wide array of tools has been developed to assist, guide, and educate those who are not experts in FAIR principles. Many of these tools are cataloged on the FAIRassist.org platform (https://fairassist.org/).\n\nAmong these tools, we highlight the FAIRplus DataSet Maturity Model (FAIR-DSM) (https://fairplus.github.io/Data-Maturity/). Developed within the IMI project FAIRplus, this tool enables the assessment of the FAIR level of a dataset. It offers an exhaustive list of tasks to help users enhance the FAIRness of their datasets in three key areas: content, representation, and hosting environment (Figure 1). By following these guidelines, users can systematically improve the quality and usability of their data.\n\nR4ALL - SOP \u2013 FAIR data assessment\n\nPage: 2/9\n\n3 9 01 06.01.25\n\nHosted by { 1 \u201c<< DESCRIPTIVE & STRUCTURAL METADATA REQUIRENENTS>> -\u2014\u2014\u2014 HOSTING ENVIRONMENT Dataset Descriptor Hosted by STORAGE CAPABILITY RETRIEVAL CAPABILITY SEARCH CAPABILITY Gea ( Noetstoclatd ne } Described by How Dataset & How Dataset & Descriptor || How Dataset & Descrigtor 1 i P Descriptor are stored are retrieved are indexed 2 DSMx}-C-7] nrcarors 3 E & ' | Conforms to Belongs to << Data Reunens> > <<(owermat Meuoan>> Lo | Dataset MODEL Domain MoDeL How the Dataset is \u2018What's included in the represented Dataset ( How the domain model is presented } ( What's reported in the Domain Model ] [SW-2-R2] Loca Mone le a {OSN-3 7] STD MODE SH-x:.\u20ac